title: Third D3gree - A different kind of love
description:
This is the first single of the Australian three piece mixed pop-R&B group formed exclusively in 2013 for the fifth season of The X Factor Australia, in which they  finished fourth. It consists of members Vanessa 'Kelebek' Skrypczak, Jacinta Gulisano and Jordan Rodrigues. Gulisano and Rodrigues contribute mainly vocals, with Skrypczak contributing both vocals and rap. All three are trained dancers.

"Different Kind of Love" was written and produced by Ben Berger and Ryan McMahon of Los Angeles duo Captain Cuts. It would have been their winner's single if they had won the show. 

(from Wikipedia.org)
